<br>
Yeah, we planned on being in Fear for 3 days.  Obviously if someone else was in there, we wouldn't go, but the fact of the matter was:<br>
<br>
1)  We hate Fear.  We hate breaking it.  But, many of the newer folks in the guild had never went, and since we could use some of the drops equipment-wise along with epic items, we decided to head up, work on it hard this week, and hopefully be done with it for a while.<br>
<br>
2)  I know they were a lot of...well, hard feelings in /gc over it.  I only caught the tail end since I had to work late due to the Code Red fiasco, but I think people were more dissapointed than anything else that their fun was 'spoiled'.<br>
<br>
3)  I also know that on some servers like Lanys, when CT is up and a guild is in fear, some of the 'uber' guilds will do the exact same thing - plow through the joint, and offer the drops to the guild that was up there.  It's a nice gesture perhaps, but what does that do to ones own pride?  Let someone else plow the zone and you pick through the scraps they leave behind?  There's no sense of accomplishment, just a sense of ninja-looting.<br>
<br>
I'm sure IV had their reasons, and since I wasn't there, I won't go into it more than that.  All I know is that they were a lot of dissapointed people last night, and I truly hope whatever 2-3 items dropped off of CT was worth it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/utrazofvazaelle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Traz of Vazaelle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Junior Member</span><br>  Posts: 100<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/31/01 1:13:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fear incident new topic </span><hr size=1>  Please lets not fill this with FLAMES, lets wait to hear both sides. Seriously you people give IV a chance to explain what happened.  There's 20 pages of post another 5 or 10 in each post to use for your petty flames. Leave this one thread alone so IV can respond.<br>
